{
  "texts": [
    "The best overall result for MULT ALL is mainly caused by the relatively good cluster quality for the classes Back- ground (SC = 0.48), Results (SC = 0.32) and Methods (SC = 0.31).",
    "In contrast, the quality of the three other clusters is not good.",
    "For SciBERT-HSLN, the cluster quality is relatively good for the class Background (SC = 0.45) and even very good for the class Conclusions (SC = 0.92), but the SC scores for the other four clusters are between -0.38 and 0.19.",
    "For MULT GRP, the results are the worst with an overall SC score of -0.02, whereby the best SC score (among MULT GRP clusters) is obtained for Background (SC = 0.18).",
    "The class Background achieved relatively good scores across all three methods."
  ]
}